<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Your attempt is misguided</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?TheBlack[BCK]">TheBlack[BCK]</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 5:41 p.m. 11/2/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Your attempt is misguided<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=660" TARGET=_self>The Only Way to do PVP!!!</A> (Platinum)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>

<BR>Attempting to introduce an alignment system in place of the faction system is not going to fly with Verant. They are wrapping this game up for final delivery, so even if they liked the idea there's really little or no hope of it going into EQ. EQ is built around the faction system and the concept of the PvP switch. Replacing that with alignment is somewhat more flexible in that it allows individuals to choose their path as opposed ot having it ascribed to them by their race, but it does not lend any sense of community which the race/faction sytem does well.
<P>Two things for everyone to keep in mind when proposing ideas:
<P>#1 The PvP switch isi law. It's here to stay.
<BR>#2 This game is being released soon. No major revisions of this game are going to be done by Verant.
<P>I expect their next game will be more complex, and have room for an idea such as an alignment system in addtion to factions.
<P>&gt; Ok instead of writing an essay right here, let me just direct
<BR>&gt; you to the url that has the FULL documented PVP idea!! This idea
<BR>&gt; covers most all other options, refines them, fine tunes them,
<BR>&gt; and generally proposes a very workable and enjoyable PvP option!
<BR>&gt; Drop me an email of anything you think should be changed, or
<BR>&gt; come on west.gamesnet.net room #everquest and msg me and we can
<BR>&gt; figure out any necessary modifications. Its right now only a pvp
<BR>&gt; skeleton, but one I feel is VERY promising. I have also
<BR>&gt; contacted several other people that posted similar ideas on
<BR>&gt; various websites to combine their input with my own. Please
<BR>&gt; check out the url, it's well worth your time. Thanks.
<P>&gt; http://www.gametab.com/eq/align.html
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
